hOW TO USE

1. Add to Pom.xml:


	    <!-- TOKEN SECURITY-->
			<dependency>
			<groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
			<artifactId>spring-boot-starter-security</artifactId>
			</dependency>
			<dependency>
			<groupId>org.springframework.security</groupId>
			<artifactId>spring-security-test</artifactId>
			<scope>test</scope>
			</dependency>
			
			<!-- JSON WEB TOKEN -->
			<dependency>
			<groupId>io.jsonwebtoken</groupId>
			<artifactId>jjwt</artifactId>
			<version>0.9.0</version>
			</dependency>
			
2. copy security folder

3. change package (line 1) 

4. add to database config:

?allowPublicKeyRetrieval=true&useSSL=false&useSSL (change ? to &)
(spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/soccer?allowPublicKeyRetrieval=true&useSSL=false&useSSL=false&useUnicode=true&useJDBCCompliantTimezoneShift=true&useLegacyDatetimeCode=false&serverTimezone=UTC)

5. postman: 

localhost:8181/login

body:

{
    "name": "user1",
    "password": "pass1"
}


you have 1 min for the next steps:

--> copy Beaver Token from header section.

Select Beaver authorization   (Authorization )
paste beaver token 

You are ready make your APiI requests!!

Have fun
